de.oaam.model.oaam.functions

Interface ExternalTaskLink

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExternalTaskLinkImpl

    public interface ExternalTaskLink
extends OaamBaseElementA, ModeDependentElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'External Task Link'. A link to an external task. This task is not part of the function model, but it is just a place holder. It must be linked from another function model.

    The following features are supported:

    • Type
    • Inputs
    • Outputs
    • Task
    • Filter
    See Also:
    FunctionsPackage.getExternalTaskLink()

      • getFilter

        java.lang.String getFilter()
        Returns the value of the 'Filter' attribute. Restricts the number of possible target functions by filter expressions related to model properties. Supports Boolean expression as: &&, ||, ! Strings can be regular expressions. For instance: id == "valve_left33"// this would be an absolute link name == "valve_left" area == "cabin" location != "left_*" name == "outflow_valve_*"
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Filter' attribute.
        See Also:
        setFilter(String), FunctionsPackage.getExternalTaskLink_Filter()
